                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17913788" author="epugh" created="Thu, 16 Jan 2025 16:08:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Someday I&apos;d love to get spell checking (and even stylistic tooling like &lt;a href=&quot;https://vale.sh/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://vale.sh/&lt;/a&gt; ) integrated! &#160; We tend to fix them a bit piece meal, and it would be good to get the code base into the best shape it can be.&#160; Especially with Solr 10x coming up, this is a good time for fixing typos in the source that maybe would be hard to back port (like method names).&#160;&#160;&#160; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I am working in the Java code, I use IntelliJ and it&apos;s features some advice on grammer for your comments, so I try to fix them one by one.&#160; More eyes and hands getting the grammer and spellings fix is very much appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17913822" author="JIRAUSER308391" created="Thu, 16 Jan 2025 17:24:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Related fix: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/pull/3038.&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/solr/pull/3038.&lt;/a&gt; Personally I have good experience with the combination of `codespell` and `typos`, both Python command line applications which are easy to install and which can also be integrated into CI tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914088" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 12:59:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit a86d21c26199b2ae17d8f18cc770a46267c890f4 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from Stefan Weil&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=a86d21c2619&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=a86d21c2619&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17622&quot; title=&quot;Spelling bugs in the Solr reference guide&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-17622&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-17622&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fix some typos in the reference guide (#3038)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most of them were found by using `codespell` and `typos`.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;---------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Signed-off-by: Stefan Weil &amp;lt;sw@weilnetz.de&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Co-authored-by: Christine Poerschke &amp;lt;cpoerschke@apache.org&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914091" author="epugh" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 13:09:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sweil&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sweil&quot;&gt;sweil&lt;/a&gt; would you consider this ticket completed?&#160;&#160; We can open more for various other sections..&#160; If you ambition is to get all the spelling bugs out of the code base, then you could rename this ticket &quot;Fix Spelling Bugs in Solr&quot; and open more PR&apos;s &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&#160;&#160; Or even make subtasks for big areas that need it to measure progress.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Or of course, we can mark this one as completed and take the win!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914126" author="JIRAUSER308391" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 14:18:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I suggest to mark this ticket as completed. My primary focus was fixing the typos in documentation which is visible by users.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixing typos in code which could even result in API changes (Solr 10x) requires significant more efforts and time. I can&apos;t promise that I&apos;ll have that time in the near future, but I would open a new issue for such a task.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17914159" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 17 Jan 2025 15:54:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 0324131689334602c202827f0d693abf7cedd779 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/branch_9x from Stefan Weil&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=03241316893&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=03241316893&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17622&quot; title=&quot;Spelling bugs in the Solr reference guide&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-17622&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-17622&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Fix some typos in the reference guide (#3038)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most of them were found by using `codespell` and `typos`.&lt;/p&gt;

